<Link id="l01340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1340"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1341"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1342"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The target location for the relocation is described by RE.SectionID and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1343"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// RE.Offset.  RE.SectionID can be used to find the SectionEntry.  Each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1344"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SectionEntry has three members describing its location.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1345"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SectionEntry::Address is the address at which the section has been loaded</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1346"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// into memory in the current (host) process.  SectionEntry::LoadAddress is the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1347"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// address that the section will have in the target process.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1348"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SectionEntry::ObjAddress is the address of the bits for this section in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1349"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// original emitted object image (also in the current address space).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1350"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1351"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Relocations will be applied as if the section were loaded at</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1352"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SectionEntry::LoadAddress, but they will be applied at an address based</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1353"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// on SectionEntry::Address.  SectionEntry::ObjAddress will be used to refer to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1354"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Target memory contents if they are required for value calculations.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1355"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1356"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The Value parameter here is the load address of the symbol for the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1357"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// relocation to be applied.  For relocations which refer to symbols in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1358"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// current object Value will be the LoadAddress of the section in which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1359"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the symbol resides (RE.Addend provides additional information about the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1360"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// symbol location).  For external symbols, Value will be the address of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1361"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// symbol in the target address space.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02792" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2792"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The adddres of the GOT1 entry is in %r11, the GOT2 entry is in %r11+8</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02793" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2793"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (see createIFuncStub() for details)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02794" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2794"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The following code first saves all registers that contain the original</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02795" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2795"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// function arguments as those registers are not saved by the resolver</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02840" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2840"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The first instruction loads a PC-relative address into %r11 which is a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02841" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2841"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// GOT entry for this stub. This initially contains the address to the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02842" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2842"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// IFunc resolver. We can use %r11 here as it&#39;s caller saved but not used</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02843" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2843"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to pass any arguments. In fact, x86&#95;64 ABI even suggests using %r11 for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02844" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2844"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// code in the PLT. The IFunc resolver will use %r11 to update the GOT</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02846" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2846"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02847" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2847"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The next instruction just jumps to the address contained in the GOT</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02849" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2849"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// %r11 so that the IFunc resolver has access to it.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02850" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2850"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02851" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2851"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The IFunc resolver of course also needs to know the actual address of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02852" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2852"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the actual IFunc resolver function. This will be stored in a GOT entry</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02853" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2853"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// right next to the first one for this stub. So, the IFunc resolver will</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02854" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2854"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// be able to call it with %r11+8.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02855" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2855"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02856" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2856"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In total, two adjacent GOT entries (+relocation) and one additional</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02857" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2857"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// relocation are required:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02858" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2858"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// GOT1: Address of the IFunc resolver.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02859" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2859"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// GOT2: Address of the IFunc resolver function.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02860" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2860"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// IFuncStubOffset+3: 32-bit PC-relative address of GOT1.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02861" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2861"><span class="doxyHighlight">    uint64&#95;t GOT1 = allocateGOTEntries(2);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02862" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2862"><span class="doxyHighlight">    uint64&#95;t GOT2 = GOT1 + <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/runtimedyldelf/#a1881f42b5c49ba8ed8d1056ee2ff90d8">getGOTEntrySize</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02863" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2863"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02864" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2864"><span class="doxyHighlight">    RelocationEntry RE1(GOTSectionID, GOT1, ELF::R&#95;X86&#95;64&#95;64,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02865" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2865"><span class="doxyHighlight">                        IFuncResolverOffset, &#123;&#125;);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02871" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2871"><span class="doxyHighlight">        0x4c, 0x8d, 0x1d, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// leaq 0x0(%rip),%r11</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02872" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2872"><span class="doxyHighlight">        0x41, 0xff, 35                          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// jmpq &#42;(%r11)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02876" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2876"><span class="doxyHighlight">    memcpy(Addr, StubCode, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(StubCode));</span></CodeLine>
